msgctxt "an9.36:9.9"
msgid "‘Ākiñcaññāyatanampāhaṃ, nissāya āsavānaṃ khayaṃ vadāmī’ti, "
msgstr "‘The dimension of nothingness is a basis for ending the defilements.’ "

msgctxt "an9.36:9.10"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an9.36:10.1"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, yāvatā saññāsamāpatti tāvatā aññāpaṭivedho. "
msgstr "And so, mendicants, penetration to enlightenment extends as far as attainments with perception. "

# NOTE: BB seems to ignore nissaya, while Thanissaro puts it right at the end. It means that these two last attainments depend on the former 7.
msgctxt "an9.36:10.2"
msgid "Yāni ca kho imāni, bhikkhave, nissāya dve āyatanāni—"
msgstr "But the two dimensions that depend on these—"

# NOTE: See BB’s note on readings. i accept bhikkhuhi, which is absent from MS.
msgctxt "an9.36:10.3"
msgid "nevasaññānāsaññāyatanasamāpatti ca saññāvedayitanirodho ca, jhāyīhete, bhikkhave, samāpattikusalehi samāpattivuṭṭhānakusalehi samāpajjitvā vuṭṭhahitvā sammā akkhātabbānīti vadāmī”ti. "
msgstr "the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception, and the cessation of perception and feeling—are properly explained by mendicants who are skilled in these attainments and skilled in emerging from them, after they’ve entered them and emerged from them.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
